Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks at a meeting with representatives of Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCUs) at the White House. Pence expressed appreciation for the contributions of HBCUs to the nation and emphasized the administration's commitment to strengthening their role in education. He also discussed the importance of expanding educational opportunities and revitalizing communities, and highlighted the administration's efforts to support these goals. Pence concluded his remarks by thanking the attendees for their work and expressing hope for a strong partnership in the future.